Githinji Mwangi Police yesterday shot dead six men suspected of attacking a boda boda rider and raping a woman in Dandora, Nairobi. The suspects reportedly ambushed the rider, robbed him of his motorbike  and raped the female pillion passenger near Lucky  Summer area. Nairobi police boss Joseph ole Tito said the motorcycle had a tracking device that enabled officers to trace the gang. On Friday, another suspect was felled in Mathare slums after he and others shot and injured a police officer in a botched robbery. Elsewhere, three suspected gangsters were gunned down by police yesterday as they attempted to break into Fortune Sacco in Kirinyaga county.